# 2012-09-07.rtb.1: Fixing the Debian Open Use Logo License

### WHEREAS

1. The Debian Project Leader, Stefano Zacchiroli, has requested that SPI 
   relicense the Debian logos listed in paragraph 2 below to meet the 
   Debian Free Software Guidelines.

2. The Debian Project Leader, Stefano Zacchiroli, has sought and 
   obtained legal advice on relicense the Debian logos and has presented 
   this advice to the Board.

3. The Board acknowledges the role of SPI in this matter is to act as a
   custodian of the Debian logos and to follow the request of the Debian 
   Project Leader in relicensing the Debian logos, subject to relevant 
   legislation and SPI by-laws.

### THE BOARD RESOLVES that:

4. The Debian logos being relicensed are:

   a) The Debian Open Use Logo depicting a red swirl with the word "Debian"
   b) The Debian Open Use Logo depicting a red swirl without the word "Debian"
   c) The Debian Official Use Logo depicting a red swirl and a bottle with the word "Debian"
   d) The Debian Official Use Logo depictnig a red swirl and a bottle without the word "Debian"

5. The Debian logos listed in paragraph 4 above are relicensed under the 
   GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL) version 3 or later, or, at the 
   recipient's option Creative Commons Attribution Share-alike license 
   (CC-BY-SA) 3.0.

6. Any use of the term "this software" within one of the licenses mentioned in paragraph 5 above shall refer to the logo itself.

